# Git author identity

When creating commits or pushing to GitHub for this project:

- Author and committer **must** be **Mittansh Bhatia** `<mittanshbhatia@users.noreply.github.com>`
- **Never** use `cursoragent`, Cursor bot, or any AI/agent identity as author or committer
- Prefer setting these per commit if needed:

```bash
export GIT_AUTHOR_NAME='Mittansh Bhatia'
export GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL='mittanshbhatia@users.noreply.github.com'
export GIT_COMMITTER_NAME='Mittansh Bhatia'
export GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL='mittanshbhatia@users.noreply.github.com'
```

- Do not invite or add `cursoragent` as a GitHub collaborator
- Do not amend history unless the user explicitly asks
